unittitle_ssm: Records of the Dean of Women, Washington Square College, Dorothy McSparran Arnold
abstract_ssm: Dorothy McSparran Arnold was Advisor to Women's Office (1924-28), Assistant Dean of Washington Square College (1928-48), and Dean of Women (1948-61) at New York University (NYU). Arnold was the administrator responsible for women's interests at Washington Square College for 43 years. The collection includes her administrative files with minutes, correspondence, memoranda, printed material, news clippings that describe, and photographs that illustrate her activities on behalf of women students.
